    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) delivers a pure, analog driving experience centered around its 3.6L flat-six M96 powerplant. The engine features VarioCam Plus for a broad torque curve and immediate throttle response. Power is managed through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, exhibiting tight synchros and a positive shift throw. The chassis remains taut, with the multi-link rear suspension and McPherson struts providing the communicative feedback and high-speed stability synonymous with the marque. Recent service records indicate a proactive inspection of the IMS bearing and a cooling system refresh to maintain optimal operating temperatures. While showing minor aesthetic patina consistent with its driver-grade status, the car's mechanical integrity is excellent, offering linear power delivery and precise turn-in for the discerning enthusiast.",
